definition: to jump/to hop/to skip over/to bounce/to palpitate
pole vault/also written 撐桿跳高|撑杆跳高

sentences.chinese: 他是一位跳高的运动员。

sentences.english: He created a new record in hellogh-jump at our school sports.
sentences.chinese: 在咱们黉舍的运动会上，他创造了跳高新纪录。

sentences.english: Henry is in for the100 meters and the high jump.
sentences.chinese: 亨利昨参加百米赛跑及跳高。

sentences.english: These typical norms are the basis for the selection of the high jump sportswomen.
sentences.chinese: 这些典型指标为跳高运动员的选材奠定了基础。

sentences.english: The pole vault is one of the most complicated events in track and field.
sentences.chinese: 撑杆跳高是田径项目中技术最为复杂的项目之一。

sentences.english: Yes，I got the second place for the high jump in the univer-sity spots meet in 1994.
sentences.chinese: 有，我于1994年获校运动会跳高比赛第二名。

sentences.english: Jack has gone in for the high-jump, but I don't think he has a chance to win.
sentences.chinese: 杰克去参加跳高比赛了，但我觉得他获胜机会很小。

sentences.english: My fortes were chinning and the high jump.
sentences.chinese: 我的长项是引体向上和跳高。

sentences.english: Only 32 points separated them as they competed in the pole vault.
sentences.chinese: 在进行撑杆跳高前，两个人的分数只差32分。

sentences.english: The pole vaulter bettered the world's record by five inches.
sentences.chinese: 这名撑杆跳高运动员以5英寸之多超过了世界纪录。

sentences.english: Li Yong set a new school record in the high jump.
sentences.chinese: 李勇在跳高比赛中创了一项新的学校纪录。

sentences.english: What are the poles made of in pole vaulting?
sentences.chinese: 撑杆跳高的杆是什么材质？

sentences.english: A high jumper, in the eyes of the experts, seems not to know what to do.
sentences.chinese: 一个跳高的人，专家认为不懂得跳。

sentences.english: He created a new record in high-jump at our school sports.
sentences.chinese: 在我们学校的运动会上，他创造了跳高新纪录。

sentences.english: How many entries are there for the high jump？
sentences.chinese: 有多少人报名参加跳高比赛了？

sentences.english: Free taking off is a kind of advanced techniques of pole vault.
sentences.chinese: 自由起跳是一种先进的撑竿跳高起跳技术。

definition: to hop/to jump on one leg
